The Vice Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party Northern Senatorial zone Hon. Chris Hassan on Monday emerged the Chairman of the party in the state to replaced Hon. Damishi Sango who recently resigned following alleged misappropriation of funds.
The emergence of Hon. Hassan followed the ratification by the state executive committee of the party on Monday at the party Secretariat in Jos endorsing the nomination of the Northern Senatorial Zone of the party inline with section 47 sub section (6) of the PDP Constitution as amended in 2017.
The Senator representing Plateau Northern Senatorial District at the National Assembly, Barr. Istifanus Dung Gyang accompanied by other National Assembly members of the party, while briefing journalists after the SEC ratification said the constitution of the party has laid down clear steps to be taken for the replacement of the party Chairman who resigns from office.